 8 March 2015On Tuesday, 10 March at 09:00am, Minister of Environmental Affairs Edna Molewa will host a media briefing on the second day of the National Waste Management Summit starting from 09-11 March 2015. The summit will provide a platform for robust and constructive high level and technical engagements on waste management priorities for the country. The briefing will be held at Ingwenyama Conference and Sports Resort, White River, Mpumalanga.On Wednesday, 11 March at 09:00am, Minister of Public Enterprises, Lynne Brown will hold a media briefing on the work of the Eskom electricity war room. The briefing will be held at Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town with a link up to Tshedimosetso House (DoC), Pretoria.Additional to these media briefings there are a number of public events that will be attended by the various Ministers. The details of the events are posted on the respective government websites.All the daily media briefings are subject to change.Enquiries: Themba Sepotokele Cell: 082 490 9869Issued by Department of Communications (DoC)